alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 25, 2025. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎علر NT ET Ruper Grint Is "Passing the Baton" to Alastair Stout to Play Ron Weasley in 'Harry Potter' Series‎'‎.
caption:
The Weasley family is getting even bigger — and Rupert Grint is cool with that. 🧙‍♂️⁠
⁠
Just like Daniel Radcliffe, the original Ron Weasley penned a letter to his predecessor, Alastair Stout, in HBO's upcoming 'Harry Potter' series, letting him know he's happily "passing the baton" to him.⁠
⁠
"I'm really intrigued [about] what it's going to be like. It's quite strange, having the cycle happen again," Rupert told BBC News. 🪄 "I had so much fun stepping into this world, and I hope he has the same experience."⁠
⁠
Rupert was 12 when he filmed the first 'Harry Potter' movie, and Alastair is 11 — so he knows exactly what this moment feels like. "It was a big thing. I still remember every second of it," he reflected. "It's a big moment, and I just want him to enjoy it."⁠
⁠
From one iconic Weasley to the next — the magic continues. (📸/🎥: Getty Images, Alastair Stout, Harry Potter, BBC News)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 25, 2025. May be an image of text that says 'ET Ενα Green Is Playing Aunt Ophelia in 'Wednesday' Season 3'.
caption:
Eva Green is about to discover the fate of (Aunt) Ophelia.⁠
⁠
Tim Burton has recruited another one of his muses for 'Wednesday' season 3: Eva is joining the cast as Morticia Addams' sister, Ophelia Frump.⁠
⁠
Burton previously directed the actress in 'Dark Shadows,' 'Miss Peregrine's Home for Peculiar Children' and 2019's 'Dumbo.'⁠
⁠
In season 2, we saw Ophelia from behind, standing in front of a bloody message: "Wednesday Must Die." It's safe to say this isn't going to be the bubbly aunt from the original 'Addams Family' series.⁠
⁠
"I'm thrilled to join the woefully twisted world of 'Wednesday' as Aunt Ophelia," Eva said. "This show is such a deliciously dark and witty world, I can’t wait to bring my own touch of cuckooness to the Addams family."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, Wednesday)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 25, 2025. May be a meme of one or more people and text that says 'ET Dick Van Dyke Jokes About Turning 100: 'IHope I Make It"'.
caption:
Dick Van Dyke is proving that age is truly just a number as he heads toward his 100th birthday on Dec. 13. ⁠
⁠
The legendary actor says his real secret to staying young isn't just his active lifestyle — it's his mindset.⁠
⁠
"I never wake up in a bad mood," he tells People. "I've always thought that anger is one thing that eats up a person's insides… I never really was able to work up a feeling of hate. I think that is one of the chief things that kept me going."⁠
⁠
A real-life reminder that joy is life's real spoonful of sugar. ⁠
⁠
When asked what surprises him most about reaching 100? "The fact that I made it." 🤣⁠
⁠
And in true Dick Van Dyke fashion, he's looking at the upcoming milestone with grace and gratitude. "I don't have any fear of death for some reason… I've had such a wonderfully full and exciting life."⁠
⁠
A century of charm, optimism, and pure magic. (📸: Getty Images)

caption:
Meet the Gosselins!⁠
⁠
Jon Gosselin and Stephanie Lebo tied the knot on Sunday, saying "I do" at Silverstone's The Barn in Lancaster, Pennsylvania.⁠
⁠
"She has shown me how to be sympathetic, because I was very non-sympathetic coming out of my divorce," he told ET of his new bride. "She's just made a better me."⁠
⁠
21-year-old Collin and Hannah — two of Jon's eight kids — were there for the ceremony and family photos, with Collin even serving as one of his dad's groomsman!⁠
⁠
"Looking at this moment and realizing how freeing this is for him and how much he deserves this and how much she deserves this, that's something I won't ever forget," Collin told ET.⁠
⁠
Swipe ⏩️ for more exclusive photos from the Gosselins big day and head to the link in bio 🔗 to watch ET's full interview with the newlyweds.⁠
⁠
(📸: Katy Trefry Photography / @katytrefryphotography)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 24, 2025. May be an image of ‎text that says '‎ET וי CAN SEE CLEARLY NOW" JIMMY CLIFF 1944-2025 2025‎'‎.
caption:
Jimmy Cliff, the legendary reggae singer best known for "I Can See Clearly Now" and "You Can Get It If You Really Want," has died at age 81.⁠
⁠
His wife, Latifa Chambers, announced his passing, sharing that Cliff died "due to a seizure followed by pneumonia."⁠
⁠
"To all his fans around the world, please know that your support was his strength throughout his whole career," she wrote on social media. "He really appreciated each and every fan for their love."⁠
⁠
In his lifetime, Cliff won GRAMMYs for Best Reggae Recording for 'Cliff Hanger' in 1985 and for Best Reggae Album for 'Rebirth' in 2013. In 2010, he was was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame.⁠
⁠
"Jimmy, my darling, may you rest in peace…" Latifa closed her message. "See you and we see you Legend."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)

caption:
Kelsey Grammer tells ET that getting to play Beast again has been "one of the great experiences of my life."⁠
⁠
The last time Kelsey really got to play Dr. Hank McCoy was nearly 20 years ago in 2006's 'X-Men: The Last Stand.' Now, he's getting to reprise the role in 'Avengers: Doomsday.'⁠
⁠
When we sat down with Kelsey to talk about his new holiday movie 'The Christmas Ring,' we had to get the scoop on his big Marvel return:⁠
⁠
𝗕𝘆𝗲, 𝗯𝘆𝗲 𝗯𝗹𝘂𝗲 𝗽𝗮𝗶𝗻𝘁: Kelsey confirmed that, like his cameo in 'The Marvels,' he's playing Beast via mo-cap and not prosthetics. "Just because it's better."⁠
⁠
𝗛𝗲𝗹𝗹𝗼, 𝗼𝗹𝗱 𝗳𝗿𝗶𝗲𝗻𝗱𝘀: Kelsey co-stars with fellow 'X-Men' alums including Patrick Stewart, Ian McKellen and Rebecca Romijn. "And James Marsden! We never really worked together."⁠
⁠
"By the time I was in 'The Last Stand,' he had been dissolved into just his glasses floating in the air, so it was nice to see him alive!"⁠
⁠
𝗫-𝗠𝗲𝗻 🤝 𝗙𝗮𝗻𝘁𝗮𝘀𝘁𝗶𝗰 𝗙𝗼𝘂𝗿: One of the new MCU stars Kelsey most enjoyed working with? "I really had a great time Pedro Pascal. And of course, we've never interacted there before."⁠
⁠
𝗣𝘂𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗗𝗼𝗼𝗺 𝗶𝗻 𝗗𝗼𝗼𝗺𝘀𝗱𝗮𝘆: Kelsey says Robert Downey Jr. is "just a terrific fella." So, is it safe to say Beast will have scenes with Doctor Doom?⁠
⁠
"It's sort of sharing a scene. I don't want to go too far!"⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images, The Marvels, The Fantastic Four: First Steps, X-Men: The Last Stand)

caption:

⁠
Kate shared the story on 'Jimmy Kimmel Live!,' recalling that she was only 20 when she met the king — then Prince Charles — for the first time at the movie's royal premiere.⁠
⁠
"I sort of hadn't realized that we were really going to meet him," she explained. "And so I forgot about the fact that I really was wearing a kind of a transparent, lace outfit."⁠
⁠
Thankfully, it was London in February, so Kate had a coat with her.⁠
⁠
"As he's making his way towards me, I'm like, 'Nipples, nipples… nipples, oh my god!' And then someone just went, 'Coat!'... I was basically covering myself in a cape and trying to hide my nipples from the King."⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Jimmy Kimmel Live!)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 22, 2025. May be an image of one or more people, poster and text that says 'ET Dick Van Dyke Reveals the Role He Regrets Turning Down: Bond!'.
caption:
Chitty Chitty Bond Bond!⁠
⁠
Dick Van Dyke is looking back on his illustrious life and revealing the one role he regrets turning down: 007. 🤵‍♂️🍸⁠
⁠
Producer Albert Broccoli approached Dick to take over the role from Sean Connery in the late '60s/early '70s.⁠
⁠
"Cubby Broccoli came to me and said, 'Would you like to be Bond?'" Dick confirmed during a sitdown on Today.⁠
⁠
"And I said, 'Have you heard my British accent?!'"⁠
⁠
Dick now says that playing Bond would "have been a great experience," though the role ultimately went to George Lazenby for 1969's 'On Her Majesty’s Secret Service.'⁠
⁠
(📸/🎥: Getty Images, Today)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 19, 2025. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'ET ET Jeremy Allen White Doesn't Actually Go By Jeremy Allen White'.
caption:
Jeremy Allen White says no one in his life actually calls him Jeremy Allen White.⁠
⁠
Yes, it is his full legal name, but he actually goes by just Jeremy White.⁠
⁠
"That's not how l understand myself," he told Vanity Fair. "It does feel like people are talking about someone I don't know."⁠
⁠
He uses his middle name professionally because there was already another Jeremy White in the Screen Actors Guild.⁠
⁠
"I'd be very interested [to meet him]. I could talk to him and maybe see if he could allow me to have Jeremy White back."⁠
⁠
(📸: Getty Images)

caption:
Arianators, we hope you have your tickets for The Eternal Sunshine Tour!⁠
⁠
During an appearance on Good Hang with Amy Poehler, Ariana referred to her upcoming tour as "one last hurrah."⁠
⁠
⁠"The last 10 or 15 years will look very different to the ones that are coming up," she explained "I do know that I'm very excited to do this small tour, but I think it might not happen again for a long, long, long, long, long time."⁠
⁠
This tour will be Ari's first since the Sweetener World Tour ended in 2019. "I'm going to give it my all," she says, "and it's going to be beautiful."⁠
⁠⁠⁠
(📸/🎥: Good Hang with Amy Poehler, Getty Images, Ariana Grande)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 20, 2025. May be an image of one or more people and text that says 'ET The Long-Lost Lost Finale of Joey' Has Been Released 20 Years Later'.
caption:
Justice for 'Joey'!⁠
⁠
The final 8 episodes of Matt LeBlanc's 'Friends' spinoff are finally available to watch on YouTube — nearly 20 years after the show was canceled.⁠
⁠
The sitcom premiered in 2004 but was midway through its second season, meaning viewers in the U.S. never got to see what happened in the finale. Until now.⁠
⁠
In 'Joey,’ LeBlanc reprised his role as Joey Tribbiani as he pursue his acting dreams in L.A., reconnecting with his sister Gina (Drea de Matteo) and his genius nephew.⁠ And Jennifer Coolidge co-starred!⁠
⁠
 ⏩️ Swipe for more. (📸/🎥: Joey)

alt: Photo by Entertainment Tonight on November 19, 2025. May be an image of poster and text that says 'O ET 'The Family Stone' Director Is Writing a Sequel to "Honor" Diane Keaton'.
caption:
The writer and director of 'The Family Stone' is hoping to "honor" the memory of Diane Keaton with a sequel.⁠
⁠
Thomas Bezucha told CNN that he's been working on a follow-up that would pick up with the Stones 20 years after the original movie.⁠
⁠
"I've been haunted by the loss of Sybil for months now while I worked on it, and so this was a blow on a tender bruise already," Bezucha says.⁠
⁠
"Mentally, I've been spending time in that house where I've been missing her for a while already."⁠
⁠
The filmmaker is hoping that the rest of the cast — which includes Sarah Jessica Parker, Luke Wilson, Claire Danes and Rachel McAdams — will be back for the sequel.⁠
⁠
(📸: The Family Stone)
